name: Delhi Darbar Hotel

reviews.review_text:
This has been my must visit place since past 12 years. Love Tangadi malai kebab here, never found it anywhere else PS it is not spicy, has cashew nut stuffing inside. My favourites here are butter chicken and garlic naan, mutton biryani.
The staff is super hospitable. Love the uncle at entrance in his grand attire and lovely moustache always welcoming us with a wide smile. Warm ambience with low retro instrumental music and match being displayed on game days. When in Goa, don‚Äôt miss Delhi Darbar :)

A decent simple ambience with the best North Indian food .we had chicken biryani which was nice not spicy though boneless properly marinated served with rayta. Fresh lime water on medium as we asked. Best part was black pepper chicken üçó ü§§ mouth watering properly cooked soft and tinder and to get a crisp of it mixed with nice salad best starter i had.
Would rate this place 4.6 out of 5 üëå Highly recommended i would have tried darbar chicken special but tummy was full maybe next time.

The food was average and they took a lot of time to prepare. The cost of the food was above the taste, but I would prefer this place to people who wants silent dine in, premium feel. The service was phenomenal!

description:
**Delhi Darbar Hotel: A Culinary Journey Through Mughlai Delights in Panaji**

Nestled in the vibrant heart of Panaji, Delhi Darbar Hotel boasts an impressive rating of 4 out of 5 stars, a testament to its widespread appeal among the 2,300 reviews it has garnered. Highly recommended for its robust kebabs, authentic Mughlai food, delectable butter chicken, and an enticing selection of Goan cuisine, this restaurant stands out as a must-visit destination for both locals and tourists seeking rich flavors and warmth.

**Ambiance & Design**

Walking into Delhi Darbar, diners are greeted by a warm and inviting atmosphere, enhanced by low retro instrumental music that softly fills the air, creating an ideal setting for relaxation. The restaurant‚Äôs d√©cor speaks to classic Indian dining, with comfortable seating arrangements that accommodate both intimate dinners and larger gatherings. Photographs shared by customers reveal lovely, warm lighting that complements the vibrant colors of the food served, ensuring a cozy yet sophisticated dining experience. Notably, the friendly staff adds to the ambiance, particularly the charming gentleman at the entrance, whose grand attire and welcoming smile set the tone for a memorable meal.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

Delhi Darbar's menu shines with an assortment of Mughlai specialties that have earned their place in the hearts of patrons. Signature dishes such as Tangadi Malai Kebab, an extraordinary preparation stuffed with cashew nuts, and the buttery richness of their butter chicken consistently receive rave reviews. Other favorites include the soft and tender black pepper chicken and mutton biryani, both praised for their flavorful profiles and perfect cooking techniques. Presentation-wise, the food boasts an appetizing appeal, beautifully plated to entice the senses. Additionally, the option for lighter fare, such as refreshing fresh lime water, allows guests to customize their dining experience.

**Customer Experience & Service**

The service at Delhi Darbar has earned accolades, with many reviews highlighting the staff's attentiveness and hospitality. One reviewer noted the efficient service that complemented the enjoyable food, although another pointed out that meal preparation could be sluggish during peak times. Nonetheless, the overall sentiment reflects a welcoming environment, where servers are eager to please and ensure a delightful dining experience. Reservation policies appear to favor walk-ins, making it accessible for spontaneous visits, especially on game days when sports are displayed on-screen for added excitement.

**Popularity & Reviews**

Delhi Darbar is not just a favorite among casual diners; the culinary establishment is frequently recommended on social media and other platforms, with several guests rating it above 4.5 out of 5. This overwhelming positive sentiment surrounds its authentic North Indian fare, notably during peak tourist seasons. While a few critiques mention that some dishes were average and the prices may not always reflect the taste, most customers appreciate the overall experience and recommend it wholeheartedly. 

**Utilizing Visual Content**

Photos from diners vividly showcase the restaurant's offerings, from the sumptuous spread of kebabs to the captivating presentation of various curries. The rich colors of the dishes captured in these images‚Äîalongside the inviting restaurant interior‚Äîtransport viewers into the essence of a great evening at Delhi Darbar. Each photograph serves to highlight the culinary artistry that diners can expect, amplifying the anticipation for those who have yet to visit.

In summary, Delhi Darbar Hotel in Panaji is a culinary gem, weaving together tradition, warmth, and mouthwatering dishes that create lasting memories for all who enter its doors. Whether you're there for a plate of tangy butter chicken or the culinary adventure of Mughlai cuisine, you're bound to leave with a satisfied palate and a desire to return.
